<!-- WHY YOUR BATH WON'T COME CLEAN -->
<section class="py-16 sm:py-20 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 sm:px-8">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-extrabold text-primary tracking-tighter mb-4">Why Your Bath Won't Come Clean</h2>
        <p class="text-secondary max-w-3xl mb-10">If you've tried every cleaning product on the shelf and the stains won't budge, it's not your technique &mdash; it's the bath itself. Here's what's actually happening.</p>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-6">
            <div class="bg-surface-container-low rounded-xl p-6 reveal">
                <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-3xl text-error mb-3 block" aria-hidden="true">layers</span>
                <h3 class="font-bold text-primary mb-2">Enamel Wear</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-relaxed">Your bath has a protective enamel coating that keeps it smooth and stain-resistant when new. Over years of use, this coating wears thin and eventually exposes the porous surface underneath. Once that happens, stains soak into the material itself &mdash; no amount of scrubbing will get them out.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-surface-container-low rounded-xl p-6 reveal">
                <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-3xl text-error mb-3 block" aria-hidden="true">water_drop</span>
                <h3 class="font-bold text-primary mb-2">Hard Water Deposits</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-relaxed">Sydney's water supply contains calcium and lime minerals. Every time water sits in or runs down your bath, a thin layer of mineral deposits is left behind. Over months and years, this builds up into a stubborn white, yellow, or brownish film that bonds to the surface and resists normal cleaners.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-surface-container-low rounded-xl p-6 reveal">
                <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-3xl text-error mb-3 block" aria-hidden="true">circle</span>
                <h3 class="font-bold text-primary mb-2">Rust Stains</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-relaxed">If you have a pressed steel or cast iron bath, rust stains are common where the enamel has worn thin &mdash; especially around the drain, overflow, and tap fittings. The steel underneath begins to oxidise on contact with water, creating orange and brown stains that spread over time.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-surface-container-low rounded-xl p-6 reveal">
                <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-3xl text-error mb-3 block" aria-hidden="true">science</span>
                <h3 class="font-bold text-primary mb-2">Chemical Damage</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-relaxed">Here's the cruel irony: harsh cleaners like bleach, abrasive powders, and strong acid-based bathroom sprays actually strip the enamel coating faster. The more aggressively you clean, the more porous the surface becomes &mdash; and the worse the staining gets over time. It's a cycle that cleaning alone can't fix.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- THE RESURFACING SOLUTION -->
<section class="py-16 sm:py-20 bg-surface-container-low">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 sm:px-8">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-extrabold text-primary tracking-tighter mb-4">The Resurfacing Solution</h2>
        <p class="text-secondary max-w-3xl mb-6">If you've never heard of bath resurfacing, here's the short version: it's a professional recoating process that gives your existing bathtub a brand new, factory-smooth finish &mdash; without removing or replacing the bath.</p>

        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-8 sm:p-10 max-w-3xl border border-surface-container reveal">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-primary mb-4 text-lg">How it works in plain English</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
                We prepare the existing bath surface through cleaning, etching, and repair. Then we apply a new, multi-layer coating of professional two-part acrylic directly over the top. Once cured, this new surface is smooth, glossy, stain-resistant, and looks identical to a brand new bathtub.
            </p>
            <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
                There's no demolition. No plumber. No ripping out tiles around the bath. The bath stays exactly where it is. The whole process takes about one day and the bath is ready to use again within 24&ndash;48 hours.
            </p>
            <div class="bg-surface-container-low rounded-lg p-4 mt-4">
                <p class="text-xs text-secondary leading-relaxed"><span class="font-bold text-primary">Note:</span> You might hear tradies call this "reglazing" or "re-enamelling" &mdash; it's the same thing. Different names for the same professional resurfacing process.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- HOW WE DO IT -->
<section class="py-16 sm:py-20 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 sm:px-8">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-extrabold text-primary tracking-tighter mb-4">How We Do It</h2>
        <p class="text-secondary max-w-3xl mb-10">Our six-step process transforms your stained bath from eyesore to showroom condition. Here's exactly what happens on the day.</p>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
            <div class="bg-surface-container-low rounded-xl p-6 reveal">
                <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-primary text-white flex items-center justify-center font-bold mb-4">1</div>
                <h3 class="font-bold text-primary text-sm mb-2">Deep Clean &amp; Chemical Etch</h3>
                <p class="text-xs text-secondary leading-relaxed">The bath is thoroughly cleaned to remove all soap scum, mineral deposits, and surface contamination. Then the surface is chemically etched to create a slightly rough profile that the new coating can grip onto. This adhesion step is critical for a long-lasting result.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-surface-container-low rounded-xl p-6 reveal">
                <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-primary text-white flex items-center justify-center font-bold mb-4">2</div>
                <h3 class="font-bold text-primary text-sm mb-2">Repair Chips, Cracks &amp; Rough Spots</h3>
                <p class="text-xs text-secondary leading-relaxed">Any <a href="<?php echo esc_url( home_url( '/services/chipped-bathtub-repair-sydney/' ) ); ?>" class="text-primary underline font-medium">chips</a>, cracks, or rough areas are filled and sanded smooth. This ensures the final finish is completely uniform with no bumps or imperfections showing through the new coating.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-surface-container-low rounded-xl p-6 reveal">
                <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-primary text-white flex items-center justify-center font-bold mb-4">3</div>
                <h3 class="font-bold text-primary text-sm mb-2">Mask Surrounding Areas</h3>
                <p class="text-xs text-secondary leading-relaxed">All surrounding tiles, fixtures, taps, and overflow fittings are carefully masked and protected. This keeps the spray coating exactly where it needs to be and protects your bathroom from overspray.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-surface-container-low rounded-xl p-6 reveal">
                <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-primary text-white flex items-center justify-center font-bold mb-4">4</div>
                <h3 class="font-bold text-primary text-sm mb-2">Apply Primer Coat</h3>
                <p class="text-xs text-secondary leading-relaxed">An industrial-grade primer is applied to create a strong chemical bond between the prepared bath surface and the topcoat. This bonding layer is what gives the resurfaced finish its durability and prevents peeling or lifting.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-surface-container-low rounded-xl p-6 reveal">
                <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-primary text-white flex items-center justify-center font-bold mb-4">5</div>
                <h3 class="font-bold text-primary text-sm mb-2">Spray Acrylic Topcoats</h3>
                <p class="text-xs text-secondary leading-relaxed">Multiple coats of professional two-part acrylic coating are sprayed onto the bath using specialist spray equipment. Each coat is applied evenly and allowed to flash off before the next. This builds up a thick, durable, stain-resistant finish.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-surface-container-low rounded-xl p-6 reveal">
                <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-primary text-white flex items-center justify-center font-bold mb-4">6</div>
                <h3 class="font-bold text-primary text-sm mb-2">Cure &amp; Polish</h3>
                <p class="text-xs text-secondary leading-relaxed">The new coating is left to cure under controlled conditions. Once set, the surface is inspected and polished to a factory-smooth, glossy finish. Masking is removed and the area is cleaned up. Your bath looks brand new.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

